body:
Rebased and refactoring using Fusesource MQTT client. After benchmarking, this client provides better performance (roughly 25% faster) and reliable behavior.
However, I'm concerned by the Checkpoint.Mark and the way to ack messages: with Fusesource MQTT client, to ack the messages, I have to store the pending messages in the checkpoint mark. This message is not fully serializable as it stores more than just the message id.
@jkff do you mind to take a look and share your thoughts ?

@kennknowles Thanks for noticing, I don't know how I miss this one, sorry, it should be ok now.

@jbonofre I chose LOG because I wanted to fix the issue but at the same time to touch the less amount of classes possible, so after running some stats in master I found that:

5   files use LOGGER
9   files use logger
100 files use LOG

So for me the natural way to go is to choose 'LOG'.
